title: In Belgorod, Russian city hit hardest by war, Putin is still running strong
description: Anti-Kremlin militias attacked ahead Russia’s presidential election aiming to show that Vladimir Putin can’t protect his country but residents said the strategy was backfiring.

title: At least 20 killed awaiting aid in Gaza as new cease-fire offer debated
description: Palestinian officials in Gaza and witnesses said Israel attacked a crowd of people waiting to collect supplies from an aid convoy in the north of the enclave.

title: As voting begins in Russian presidential election, so do the protests
description: Some voters set fire to polling stations while others spoiled their ballots as President Vladimir Putin was guaranteed to clinch a fifth term against token opponents approved by the Kremlin.

title: Indigenous people accuse radiologists of secretly studying their organs
description: In a lawsuit, dozens of Pictou Landing First Nation members accused two radiologists of conducting MRI scans of their livers without their consent in Nova Scotia.

title: Israeli officials slam Schumer’s call for new election as ‘counterproductive’
description: Schumer’s remarks from the the Senate floor marked the clearest signal yet of mounting U.S. frustrations toward Netanyahu.

title: Who is José Andrés, the chef behind the first aid ship to Gaza?
description: World Central Kitchen, which coordinated the voyage with the Spanish search-and-rescue group Open Arms, has also fed U.S. hurricane survivors and refugees fleeing Ukraine.

title: U.S. anticipates grim course for Ukraine if aid bill dies in Congress
description: The Biden administration assesses that, absent more U.S. military support for Ukraine, “countless lives” will be lost as it struggles to stave off collapse.

title: Middle East conflict live updates: U.S. announces sanctions on West Bank settler outposts
description: A ship that left Cyprus for Gaza this week carrying 200 tons of food is expected to arrive early Friday, according to aid workers.

title: Celebrity chef’s first aid boat to Gaza nearing arrival, organizers say
description: The boat, which is carrying nearly 200 tons of food, departed Tuesday from Cyprus and was expected to arrive along Gaza’s coastline early Friday.

title: On Gaza aid, U.S. seeks complex workarounds to straightforward problem
description: The Gaza Strip is surrounded by existing routes, in the care of staunch U.S. allies, by which a massive increase in aid could arrive by truck.
